IMPORTANT NOTE :-
1) INITIALIZING OF MUTEX/COND/BARRIER :-
   All mutex/cond/barrier variables are to be initialized dynamically.
   Static initilization is not supported.
   Instead of using 'mythread_*_t = INITIAL_VALUE' use 'mythread_*_init()'

2) *_init(arg1, arg2) function takes arg2 as NULL

_______________________________________________________________________________________

COMMANDS FOR FRESH COMPILE AND RUN

1) COMMAND : make clean

2) To make static library using all the mythread_*.c files :-
COMMAND : make library
OUTPUT  : static library *libmysync.a* on success.

3) To make the executable using the static library :-
COMMAND : make binary
OUTPUT  : Executable *p4* on success.

4) Run the Test Program :-
./p4
__________________________________________________________________________________________
